fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. Technical debt (aka tech debt, code debt) is what you owe on your Momentum Learning coding tuition
fields.answer: Falsy (well, sort of). Tech debt describes what results when development teams take actions to expedite the delivery of a piece of functionality or a project which later needs to be refactored

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. The first formal description of the Waterfall software development methodology is often cited to have been published in 1970. A revision called, Waterfalls by TLC, was released 25 years later.
fields.answer: Falsy. Waterfalls was an original R&B hit that had no relation to Waterfall swdev model.

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. UI/UX a spinoff of SXSW
fields.answer: Falsy. UI/UX is a user interface and user experience design concept. South by Southwest is the annual convergence of the interactive, film, and music industries.

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. Git is a term of insult with origins in English denoting an unpleasant, silly, incompetent, annoying, senile, elderly or childish person.
fields.answer: Truthy. Git is also a version control system for team code collaboration and development.

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. A quote coined by Clinton Dreisbach during MLC7 suggested that \"Imagination has no address.
fields.answer: Truthy. Clinton Dreisbach did coin the phrase. Falsy. Imagination is a 50-year-old independent experience company with 12 offices worldwide (imagination.com).

fields.question: Acronym. JSON is short for...?
fields.answer: JavaScript Object Notion

fields.question: Frontend. What purpose does JSON (JavaScript Object Notion) have?
fields.answer: JSON is an open standard file format, and data interchange format, that uses human-readable text to store and transmit data objects consisting of attribute value pairs, array data types (or any other serializable value)

fields.question: Frontend. What language of rules affect the style of HTML content?
fields.answer: CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)

fields.question: Backend. What techniques are used to send data asynchronously to and from a server in the background without any changes to the web page for the user?
fields.answer: AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript And XML)

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy.  appendChild() is an obsolete method of the JavaScript DOM.
fields.answer: Falsy. appendChild() is a deprecated method of the Javascript DOM

fields.question: Frontend. XML (Extensible Markup Language) is a term that does what?
fields.answer: XML is a metalanguage which allows a developer to define their own customized markup languages, especially in order to display documents on the Internet.

fields.question: Frontend. CDN (Content Delivery Network) is a group of servers spread out over many locations and widely used for delivering what type resource(s)?
fields.answer: CDN is widely used for delivering stylesheets and Javascript files (static assets) of libraries such as, Tachyons, Shoelace, Bootstrap, and JQuery.

fields.question: Backend. What is the purpose of an API (Application Programming Interface)?
fields.answer: API is a set of functions and procedures allowing the creation of web applications that access the features or data of an operating system, application, or other service.

fields.question: Backend. What are the four basic functions of CRUD?
fields.answer: Create, Read, Update, Delete are the four basic functions a software developer builds into every app for user interaction

fields.question: Backend. DOM (Document Object Model) is a programming API that defines the logical structure of documents and the way a document is accessed and manipulated for what two interface types?
fields.answer: HTML and XML documents

fields.question: Backend. What two endpoints does FTP (File Transfer Protocol) affect?
fields.answer: FTP transfers files over the web from a client endpoint to a server endpoint.

fields.question: Backend. What mapping technique converts data between incompatible type systems in object-oriented programming languages
fields.answer: ORM (Object Relational Mapping) is a technique for converting data between systems in object-oriented programming languages.

fields.question: Backend. REGEX (REGular EXpression) is a set of rules used to process what type data?
fields.answer: REGEX rules the process of strings, such as alphabets and numbers.

fields.question: Backend. Web services that conform to the REpresentational State Transfer (REST) software architectural style are called...
fields.answer: RESTFul web services. Examples include APACHE CXF, Jello Framework, Windows Communication Foundation.

fields.question: Backend. What is the purpose of a URI (Uniform Resource Identifier)?
fields.answer: A URI is a sequence (string) of characters that identifies a logical or physical resource.

fields.question: Backend. The acronym WYSIWYG (wi-zee-wig) means, "What You See Is What You Get." But what exactly does it do?
fields.answer: WYSIWYG is an editor that allows you to design a web page or text as you see it, without needing to write HTML

fields.question: Frontend.  What techniques are used to send data asynchronously to and from a server in the background without any changes to the web page for the user?
fields.answer: AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript And XML)

fields.question: Frontend. A CMS (content management system) is a software application or set of related programs that are used for what purpose?
fields.answer: A CMS creates and manages digital content.

fields.question: Frontend. What is the purpose of software application load testing?
fields.answer: Load testing is performed to determine the behavior of a software application on a system under both normal and at peak conditions.

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. On the web, front-end developer code tells your browser how to do things.
fields.answer: Falsy. Front-end developer code tells your browser what to do. Back-end developer code tells your browser 'HOW' to do it.

fields.question: Frontend. What type web-based platform collects information from different sources into a single user interface and presents users with the most relevant information for their context.
fields.answer: A portal system.

fields.question: Code. What is result of the command "python3 -m venv venv"?
fields.answer: This command will create a folder venv in your working directory. Inside this directory, you’ll find several files including a copy of the Python standard library. Later, when you install new dependencies, they will also be stored in this directory.

fields.question: Code. What does the dot notation "{{ project.title }}" do in this code?
fields.answer: The dot notation is used to access the project’s "title" attribute. The same notation can be used to access any other project attribute.

fields.question: Code. The CSS code "transform: rotateY(180deg)" does what?
fields.answer: "transform: rotateY(180deg)" defines a transformation that rotates an element 180 degrees around the ordinate (vertical axis) without deforming it.

fields.question: Code. What is the result of this CSS code "backface-visibility: hidden;"?
fields.answer: The backface-visibility property defines whether or not the back face of an element should be visible or hidden when facing the user. In this case it is hidden.

fields.question: Truthy or Falsy. A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) is a language for specifying addresses on the internet, or an address that identifies a particular file on the Internet, usually consisting of http, followed by the domain name.
fields.answer: Falsy. A URL is a "protocol," not a language for specifying Internet addresses.
